    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 10 SPEED AND 15 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RT, RTO, AND RTX
        SERIES - REMOVE - INPUT SHAFT
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="7">
        <title>INPUT SHAFT</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1301587">Figure 87</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1301587" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1301587" filename="../figg13/G1301587.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 87. Input Shaft Exploded View</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the input shaft bearing retaining snap ring from the input shaft groove (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301588">Figure 88</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301588" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301588" filename="../figg13/G1301588.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 88. Remove Input Shaft Bearing Retaining Snap Ring</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Drive the input shaft into the transmission and through the bearing as far as possible (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301589">Figure 89</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301589" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301589" filename="../figg13/G1301589.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 89. Drive Input Shaft into Transmission</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the input shaft from the transmission case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301590">Figure 90</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301590" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301590" filename="../figg13/G1301590.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 90. Remove Input Shaft From Transmission Case</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the drive gear and the drive gear spacer (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301591">Figure 91</hotlnk>). Remove the snap ring (inset).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301591" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301591" filename="../figg13/G1301591.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 91. Remove Drive Gear and Drive Gear Spacer</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Drive the input shaft bearing out the front of the case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301592">Figure 92</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301592" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301592" filename="../figg13/G1301592.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 92. Drive Input Shaft Bearing Out Front of Case</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check the bushing in the pocket of the input shaft and replace if worn or damaged (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301593">Figure 93</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301593" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301593" filename="../figg13/G1301593.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 93. Check Bushing in Pocket of Input Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
